cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes a probabilistic algorithm for reconstructing a sequence of multidimensional real vectors with missing data. This involves regression and mapping inversion, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm uses a joint density model, specifically the generative topographic mapping, to capture the low-dimensional nature of the data, which is a common technique in computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of dynamic programming to minimize a global constraint, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and control theory (cs.NE, cs.SD).
